    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Data Story'>
      <repository-location derived-from='https://public.tableau.com/workbooks/ElsewhereGlobalLifestyleCostIntelligenceDashboard/DataStory?rev=' id='131829792' path='/workbooks/ElsewhereGlobalLifestyleCostIntelligenceDashboard' revision='' />
      <style>
        <style-rule element='table'>
          <format attr='background-color' value='#1a1a2e' />
        </style-rule>
      </style>
      <size maxheight='1000' maxwidth='1000' minheight='1000' minwidth='1000' sizing-mode='fixed' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='30700' id='3' name='Finding 1 - Sweet Spot' w='45500' x='1600' y='900' />
        <zone h='29600' id='4' name='Finding 2 - Internet Correlation' w='48600' x='49500' y='1300' />
        <zone forceUpdate='true' h='7625' id='5' type-v2='text' w='46500' x='2000' y='30500'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#ffffff' fontname='Calibri' fontsize='8'>East Asian and Southeast Asian cities offer the best combination of low cost and high lifestyle quality, based on regional medians — outperforming pricier regions like North America and Western Europe despite similar or better composite scores.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone forceUpdate='true' h='5750' id='6' type-v2='text' w='46100' x='51500' y='29875'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#ffffff' fontname='Calibri' fontsize='8'>Internet speed and cost of living show a moderate positive correlation (r = 0.54) — faster connections tend to come with higher costs, though notable exceptions exist at both ends.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone h='27250' id='7' name='Finding 3 - Safety Premium' w='45100' x='1600' y='37750' />
        <zone h='26000' id='8' name='Finding 4 - Purchasing Power Illusion' w='47000' x='51600' y='37900' />
        <zone forceUpdate='true' h='6000' id='9' type-v2='text' w='45900' x='2600' y='66000'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#ffffff' fontname='Calibri' fontsize='8'>The 10 safest cities cost roughly the same as the dataset average (55.5 vs 56.0 index) — safety doesn&apos;t come with a price premium. Abu Dhabi, Ajman, Taipei, and Doha combine top-10 safety with affordability.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone forceUpdate='true' h='6375' id='10' type-v2='text' w='42600' x='54100' y='65250'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#ffffff' fontname='Calibri' fontsize='8'>The biggest gaps between nominal cost and real purchasing power appear in Indian and Chinese secondary cities — Hyderabad, Pune, Chengdu, and Nanjing offer far more purchasing power than their low sticker price alone suggests.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone h='27000' id='11' name='Finding 5 - Home Context' w='47000' x='2000' y='72625' />
        <zone h='19900' id='12' name='Home Context Text' show-title='false' w='44800' x='52500' y='79000' />
      </zones>
